# Eval case: receipt-ocr-expense

IDEA="Create a local expense tracker that ingests photos or PDFs of receipts, extracts merchant, date, line items, and total using on-device OCR, and lets a local LLM normalize messy merchant names and suggest a category from a fixed taxonomy using structured extracted fields only. Stores expenses in a local DB and exports a monthly Markdown expense summary."

CONTEXT="Target: single user, laptop-only, fully offline. Stack: Python CLI; Tesseract OCR; Pillow; SQLite (encrypted); Ollama 7B optional for name normalization. Formats: JPEG/PNG receipt images; PDF receipts. Limits: max 15 expense categories; max 10MB per file. Non-goals: cloud OCR APIs; cloud LLM default; React UI; multi-user; bank integration; tax filing; sending receipt images off-device. Defer: mileage tracking; multi-currency; bulk import."
